X:1
T:Auld Lang Syne — denser ornamentation
T:Intermediate setting (Heifer Zephyr)
C:Robert Burns (lyrics, 1788), trad. Scottish (melody)
S:Public domain (US) — both lyrics (1788) and melody pre-1929.
N:Intermediate-level pipe-band setting of the same melody as
N:01-easy/auld-lang-syne. The principal-note contour is identical;
N:every long note now carries an ornament cluster, including a birl
N:on the repeated low A's at the start. NO RESTS — held tones
N:replace what would be silences.
M:4/4
L:1/8
Q:1/4=80
K:Amix
H:Range: low A (A4) to high A (A5). All nine chanter notes used.
H:Arrangement: Heifer Zephyr / Tony Koop, 2026 (MIT, sheet-music repo).
H:Compared to the easy version, this setting:
H:  - adds birls on the repeated low A's in bars 1, 3, 9, 11
H:  - adds doublings to every quarter-length principal note
H:  - inserts grips on the repeated B–c upbeats
H:  - holds the final cadence under a {GBG}A8 grip-doubling
% --- 16-bar through-form, denser ornaments throughout ---
{GdG}A2 |\
{GAGA}A2 {GAG}A2 {GdG}A2 {GdG}c2 | {GdG}c2 {GBG}B2 {GdG}A2 {GBG}B2 | {GdG}c2 {GdG}A2 {GAG}A2 {GdG}c2 | {GeG}e6 {ge}e2 |
{ge}e2 {gf}f2 {ge}e2 {gag}a2 | {gag}a2 {gag}a2 {gag}g2 {gf}f2 | {GdG}A2 {GBG}B2 {GdG}c2 {GBG}B2 | {GBG}A6 {GdG}A2 |
{GAGA}A2 {GAG}A2 {GdG}A2 {GdG}c2 | {GdG}c2 {GBG}B2 {GdG}A2 {GBG}B2 | {GdG}c2 {GdG}A2 {GAG}A2 {GdG}c2 | {GeG}e6 {ge}e2 |
{ge}e2 {gf}f2 {ge}e2 {gag}a2 | {gag}a2 {gag}a2 {gag}g2 {gf}f2 | {GdG}A2 {GBG}B2 {GdG}c2 {GBG}B2 | {GBG}A8 |]
